Exploit Path Simulation & Cross-Contract Failure Model
1. 📌 Overview

This document defines the System Attack Graph for the PanjoCoin (PNJC) protocol.

Unlike a traditional threat model, this document does NOT describe risks in isolation.

Instead, it models:

Multi-step exploit chains
Cross-contract attack propagation
System-wide failure cascades
Liquidity + staking + vesting interaction vulnerabilities
Realistic attacker behavior simulation
2. 🧠 Attack Graph Model Definition

The protocol is modeled as a directed graph:

G=(N,E)

Where:

N (Nodes) = smart contracts + system states
E (Edges) = callable interactions between modules
Nodes:
PNJC Token
PNJC_Staking
PNJC_Vesting
PNJC_Free_Router
PNJC_Airdrop
PNJC_Multisig
Liquidity Pool (AMM)
Edges:
transfer()
stake()
claim()
swap()
unlock()
executeGovernance()
