6. 📊 System Resilience Interpretation

The PanjoCoin system is resilient if:

No single attack path leads to irreversible collapse
Liquidity and staking absorb supply shocks
Governance cannot be externally hijacked
Router execution remains MEV-bounded
7. 🧠 Formal Security Statement

The system is modeled as a multi-layer adversarial graph where exploitability depends not on isolated contract vulnerabilities, but on the emergent interaction of vesting schedules, liquidity depth, staking incentives, and governance execution thresholds.

8. 🏁 Final Statement

The System Attack Graph demonstrates that PanjoCoin’s risk profile is not static, but dynamically emergent across interconnected protocol layers, where multi-step exploit chains are the primary security consideration rather than single-contract failures.

